Vice President Mike Pence has concluded his visit to Japan and is now in South Korea. During his time in Japan, Pence toured joint U.S-Japan operations and met with military personnel. He delivered a message of American resolve and thanked the troops for their service. In South Korea, Pence met with President Moon Jae-in to discuss intensifying pressure on North Korea to abandon its nuclear and ballistic missile programs. Pence and his wife will also be leading the U.S. delegation to the 2018 Olympic Winter Games in Pyeongchang. This is Pence's second visit to Japan and South Korea in less than a year.